Key Benefits of Docker
✅ Portable → Runs anywhere without setup issues.
✅ Lightweight → Uses fewer resources than virtual machines.
✅ Fast Deployment → Start an app instantly in any environment.
✅ Easy Scaling → Run multiple instances effortlessly.

------------------------------------------------
| AWS EC2 Instance (Virtual Machine)          |
| ------------------------------------------- |
| | Linux OS (Ubuntu, Amazon Linux, etc.)  | |  <-- 🟢 OS layer to run Docker.
| |-----------------------------------------| |
| | Docker Engine (Bridge)                  | |  <-- 🟢 Manages containers.
| |-----------------------------------------| |
| | Container 1 (Spring Boot App + JDK)     | |  <-- 🟢 Runs the Java app.
| | Container 2 (Database - MySQL/Postgres) | |  <-- 🟢 Stores application data.
| | Container 3 (Redis, Other Services)     | |  <-- 🟢 Caching & microservices.
| ------------------------------------------- |
------------------------------------------------





┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  1️⃣ Create a Spring Boot Application             |  
|     🔹 Why? → Develop the Java-based application. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  2️⃣ Create a Dockerfile                          |  
|     🔹 Why? → Define how the app runs inside a container. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  3️⃣ Build a Docker Image                         |  
|     🔹 Why? → Package the app into a portable container image. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  4️⃣ Push Image to Docker Hub                     |  
|     🔹 Why? → Store the image in a cloud repository for deployment. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  5️⃣ Launch an AWS EC2 Instance                   |  
|     🔹 Why? → Create a virtual machine to host the application. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  6️⃣ Install Linux OS on EC2                      |  
|     🔹 Why? → The base operating system required for Docker. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  7️⃣ Install Docker Engine on Linux OS            |  
|     🔹 Why? → Enables running and managing containers. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  8️⃣ Pull Image from Docker Hub                   |  
|     🔹 Why? → Retrieve the stored application image. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
|  9️⃣ Run the Docker Container                     |  
|     🔹 Why? → Start the application inside the EC2 instance. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓  
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
| 🔟 Access the Application                         |  
|     🔹 Why? → Verify and use the running application. |
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
